# Dirt & Leaf — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values before production use.
# The app runs and is fully testable end to end with NONE of these set —
# every integration below has a clearly-labeled mock/fallback path.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Plant.id (kindwise.com) — plant identification from a photo.
# Get a key at https://web.plant.id/ (or https://kindwise.com/plant-id).
# Without this, server/plant-id.ts returns deterministic MOCK suggestions
# (clearly labeled `mock: true` in the API response and surfaced to the
# user as a toast: "Using demo identification").
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PLANT_ID_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Amazon Associates — affiliate link tag used on every "Buy fertilizer /
# soil / pot / tools" CTA in the Shop tab and task sheets.
# Sign up at https://affiliate-program.amazon.com/. Without this, links use
# the SPEC placeholder tag "YOUR-ASSOCIATES-TAG-20" so the app is testable
# but generates no real affiliate revenue.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AMAZON_ASSOCIATES_TAG=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Web Push (VAPID) — required for real push notifications in production.
# Generate a permanent keypair ONCE with:
#   npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
# Re-generating these after users have subscribed will invalidate their
# existing subscriptions. Without these set, server/push.ts falls back to a
# bundled DEV-ONLY keypair (fine for local testing, NOT for production).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=
# Contact email required by the Web Push protocol (shown to push services,
# not to end users). Any real inbox you control.
VAPID_CONTACT_EMAIL=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# No key required for weather/season data (Open-Meteo) or nearby nurseries
# (OpenStreetMap Nominatim + Overpass) — both are called with no auth in
# server/weather.ts and server/nurseries.ts.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Payments — NOT YET IMPLEMENTED. The current build stubs the Premium
# upgrade as a mock DB write (see server/routes.ts POST /api/account/upgrade
# and README.md "Pricing & subscriptions"). Before accepting real payments:
#   - Web: integrate Stripe Checkout + webhooks, add STRIPE_SECRET_KEY,
#     STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, STRIPE_PRICE_ID_MONTHLY, STRIPE_PRICE_ID_YEARLY.
#   - Native iOS/Android (future): Apple/Google in-app-purchase receipt
#     validation instead of Stripe for in-app subscriptions.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
